To identify the synergistic DCF degradation achieved in the US/ANF process, comparative experiments in the separated and combined processes were conducted at optimized values of variables and a fixed value of DCF concentration. The mean differences between DCF removal in the ANF and US/ANF process at optimized conditions reached 9.2 and 10.7% at 35 and 130 kHz, respectively (data not shown). In the case of applying multiple processes, synergy index is a common quantitative method to evaluate any synergistic effect which is as follow:3Synergyindex=Removal%(US/ANF)Removal%US+Removal%(ANF)\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
